<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1685,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1685,1711]" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Description.</emphasis>
Body length up to 
<quantity box="[564,668,1685,1712]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.42" pageId="7" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="1.42">1.42 mm</quantity>
. Ground colour pale yellow in ethanol. Distal part of Ant. I−II, Ant. III−IV blackish violet. Eye patches dark blue. Anterior and lateral parts of dorsal head with blue pigment. Blue pigment also present on each tergite and coxa (
<figureCitation box="[641,773,1757,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 35−36" captionStartId="9.[151,264,975,999]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,184,951]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,951]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35−36. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 35−36, habitus. Scale bars: 35−36= 500μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795367/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Figs 35−36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1685,2036]" box="[199,667,1793,1819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">
Body chaetae long and leaf-like (
<figureCitation box="[571,655,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 37−40" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,184,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[167,1419,181,1410]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37−40. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 37, leaf-like chaetae on body; 38, eyes; 39, middle claw; 40, mucrones. Scale bars: 37−40 = 10μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795369/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1685,2036]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="379" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">
Antenna 0.41−0.45 times body length; antennal segment ratio as I: II: III: IV = 1: 1.70−2.22: 1.60−2.00: 2.07−2.85. Apical bulb of Ant. IV bilobed (
<figureCitation box="[654,740,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. III with three rods (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1294,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. II with two rods (
<figureCitation box="[438,523,1901,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
). Eyes 8+8, G and H smaller than others, interocular chaetae as p, s, t mes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 37−40" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,184,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[167,1419,181,1410]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37−40. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 37, leaf-like chaetae on body; 38, eyes; 39, middle claw; 40, mucrones. Scale bars: 37−40 = 10μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795369/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Figs 38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[194,226,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">44</figureCitation>
). Dorsal cephalic chaetotaxy with four antennal (An), four median (M) and eight sutural (S) mac (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Prelabral and labral chaetae as 4/5, 5, 4, prelabral chaetae ciliate, other smooth, four labral papillae with one minute denticle each (
<figureCitation box="[316,401,2009,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="378">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Lateral process (l.p.) of labial papilla E differentiated, thicker than normal chaeta with tip reaching apex of papilla E (
<figureCitation box="[465,551,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Labial triangular chaetae as MREL1L2, all ciliate and R 0.50−0.55 length of M (
<figureCitation box="[192,277,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Subapical chaeta of maxillary outer lobe thin, subequal to apical one; three smooth hairs on sublobal plate (
<figureCitation box="[221,305,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 41−48" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[156,1424,191,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 41−48. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 41, apex of Ant. IV; 42, distal part of Ant. III; 43, distal part of Ant. II; 44, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 45, labrum; 46, lateral process of labial palp; 47, labium; 48, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 41−48 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795373/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795363" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6795363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795363/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="379" startId="8.[151,264,1906,1930]" targetBox="[159,1428,282,1876]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1906,2003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1906,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">FIGURES 28−34.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Ma, 2022" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" box="[347,537,1907,1931]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Willowsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifascia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[347,537,1907,1931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">Willowsia trifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[543,624,1907,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[543,624,1907,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="379" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
28, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 29, anterior face of ventral tube; 30, posterior face of ventral tube; 31, lateral flap of ventral tube; 32, manubrial plaque; 33, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 34, mucro. Scale bars: 28−34 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[222,236,1979,2003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="379">=</emphasis>
20μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795367" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6795367" box="[151,1127,975,999]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795367/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" startId="9.[151,264,975,999]" targetBox="[161,1433,184,951]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1127,975,999]" box="[151,1127,975,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,975,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">FIGURES 35−36.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Ma, 2022" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" box="[348,589,975,999]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Himalanura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gansuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[348,589,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Himalanura gansuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,676,975,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,676,975,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
35−36, habitus. Scale bars: 35−36 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1028,1042,975,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">=</emphasis>
500μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1045,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
Th. II with four (m1, m2, m2i, m2i2) mac on T1 area, five (a5, m4, m4i, m4p, m5) mac on T2 area, 24−30 posterior mac, one ms and two se on each side. Th. III with 32−36 mac and two se (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1146,1081,1107]" captionStart="FIGURES 49−51" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,895,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-380@12.[151,1436,885,1868]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 49−51. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 49, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 50, trochanteral organ; 51, hind foot complex. Scale bars: 49−51 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795375/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Trochanteral organ with 11−13 smooth spiny chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[486,571,1117,1144]" captionStart="FIGURES 49−51" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,895,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-380@12.[151,1436,885,1868]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 49−51. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 49, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 50, trochanteral organ; 51, hind foot complex. Scale bars: 49−51 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795375/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Unguis with four inner teeth, one pair located 0.57−0.59 from base of inner edge of unguis, distal unpaired two respectively at 0.71−0.76 and 0.83−0.91 distance from base. Unguiculus acuminate and outer edge serrate. Tenent hair thick with its tip clavate, longer than inner side of unguis (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1338,1189,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 37−40" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,184,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[167,1419,181,1410]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37−40. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 37, leaf-like chaetae on body; 38, eyes; 39, middle claw; 40, mucrones. Scale bars: 37−40 = 10μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795369/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Figs 39</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1350,1381,1189,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 49−51" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,895,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-380@12.[151,1436,885,1868]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 49−51. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 49, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 50, trochanteral organ; 51, hind foot complex. Scale bars: 49−51 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795375/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">51</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1045,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
Abd. IV 2.50−4.28 times Abd. III in dorsal axial length. Abd. I with nine (a2, a3, a5, m2−4, m2i, m4i, m4p), ms antero-external to se. Abd. II with two (a2, a3) mac on A1 arae, four (m3, m3e, m3ea, m3ep) mac on A2 area, one (m5) lateral mac and two se. Abd. III with two (a2, a3) mac on A4 area, one (m3) mac on A5 area and three (am6, pm6, p6) lateral mac, one ms and two se (
<figureCitation box="[614,698,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[294,1290,202,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[277,1311,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 52. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 52. chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bar: 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795377/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Abd. IV with seven central mac, 10 lateral mac (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1337,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). Abd. V with three se (
<figureCitation box="[312,397,1369,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Anterior face of ventral tube with 11−14 ciliate chaetae, line connecting proximal (Pr) and external-distal (Ed) mac oblique to median furrow (
<figureCitation box="[739,824,1405,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
); posterior face not clearly seen; lateral flap with 2−3 smooth chaetae and 7−8 ciliate chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[605,689,1441,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
). Manubrial plate dorsally with 6−7 ciliate chaetae and three pseudopores (
<figureCitation box="[254,339,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
); ventrally with 10−11 ciliate chaetae on each side (
<figureCitation box="[911,994,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Uncrenulated dens 2.43−3.21 times as mucro in length. Mucro bidentate, two teeth subequal and tip of basal spine reaching subapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1379,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURES 37−40" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,184,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[167,1419,181,1410]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37−40. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 37, leaf-like chaetae on body; 38, eyes; 39, middle claw; 40, mucrones. Scale bars: 37−40 = 10μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795369/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Figs 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1390,1422,1513,1540]" captionStart="FIGURES 53−59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[157,1429,190,1911]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53−59. Himalanura gansuensis sp. nov. 53, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 54, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 55, anterior face of ventral tube; 56, lateral flap of ventral tube; 57, manubrial plaque; 58, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 59, mucro. Scale bars: 53−59 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795379/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">59</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="380" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1045,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1549,1575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Ecology.</emphasis>
Found in rotten leaf, mainly composed of 
<taxonomicName box="[775,982,1549,1575]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tabuliformis">
<emphasis box="[775,982,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Pinus tabuliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1245,1549,1576]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="liaotungensis">
<emphasis box="[996,1245,1549,1576]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Quercus liaotungensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zabelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Cotoneaster zabelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,805,1621,1647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1045,1899]" box="[199,805,1621,1647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1621,1647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after its locality: 
<collectingRegion box="[619,801,1621,1647]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Gansu Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="380" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1045,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1657,1683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is the second 
<taxonomicName box="[678,905,1657,1683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis box="[678,815,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">Himalanura</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1146,1657,1683]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">China</collectingCountry>
and can be distinguished from the first Chinese species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Ma, 2020" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[642,1015,1693,1720]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Himalanura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shanxiensis">
<emphasis box="[642,805,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">H. shanxiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhou, R. &amp; Ma, Y. T." box="[812,1015,1693,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" pagination="57 - 66" refId="ref7170" refString="Zhou, R. &amp; Ma, Y. T. (2020) A new record genus and a new species of Entomobryidae (Collembola) from China. Transactions American Entomological Society, 147, 57 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.3157 / 061.147.0105" type="journal article" year="2020">
Zhou &amp; Ma, 
<quantity box="[959,1015,1693,1719]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1308" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" unit="in" value="2020.0">2020</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in colour pattern, body macrochaetotaxy and other characters. It is similar to these species in macrochaetotaxy of Abd. III: 
<taxonomicName authority="Baquero, Mandal &amp; Jordana, 2014" authorityName="Baquero, Mandal &amp; Jordana" authorityYear="2014" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Himalanura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baijali">
<emphasis box="[1104,1210,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">H. baijali</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baquero, E. &amp; Mandal, G. &amp; Jordana, R." pageId="9" pageNumber="380" pagination="1554 - 1587" refId="ref6039" refString="Baquero, E., Mandal, G. &amp; Jordana, R. (2014) Singular fauna of Entomobryidae (Collembola) from &quot; Land of Passes &quot; in the Himalayas, India. Florida Entomologist, 97 (4), 1554 - 1587. https: // doi. org / 10.1653 / 024.097.0430" type="journal article" year="2014">Baquero, Mandal &amp; Jordana, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tshelnokov, 1977" authorityName="Tshelnokov" authorityYear="1977" box="[320,665,1765,1791]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Himalanura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulunkuli">
<emphasis box="[320,459,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">H. bulunkuli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tshelnokov, V. G." box="[465,665,1765,1791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" pagination="1030 - 1037" refId="ref6977" refString="Tshelnokov, V. G. (1977) New species of the genus Entomobrya (Collembola, Entomobryidae) in the Asian part of the USSR. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 56 (7), 1030 - 1037." type="journal article" year="1977">Tshelnokov, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tshelnokov, 1987" authorityName="Tshelnokov" authorityYear="1987" box="[675,1004,1765,1791]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Himalanura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gelmani">
<emphasis box="[675,798,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="380">H. gelmani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tshelnokov, V. G." box="[804,1004,1765,1791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="380" pagination="96 - 101" refId="ref7017" refString="Tshelnokov, V. G. (1987) New species of springtails of the genus Entomobrya Rondani (Collembola, Entomobryidae) from the North-East of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 66 (1), 96 - 101." type="journal article" year="1987">Tshelnokov, 1987</bibRefCitation>
